Python 3.9 script which uses the lark library - a modern parsing library for Python.
This script aims at parsing some given set of items with the help of lark library.
Also, tests are written to make sure the functionality is working as expected.
A Utility class for performing operations with Lark parsing library.
A simple example of a pytorch_lightning module
A test to check the functionality of Lark parser with some randomly generated strings
A function to Mock the test, providing a control over the returned value.
